    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 12th with a high-floor offensive outlook, headlined by the trio of **Christian Yelich** (73.34), **Trea Turner** (71.43), and **Kyle Schwarber** (67.82). **Christian Yelich** earns our strongest endorsement of the day, benefiting from a massive 13% boost due to a favorable platoon matchup against Zack Littell, which vaults his daily efficiency well above his base projection. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** remain locked in the top tier; despite a tough assignment against Zac Gallen, both elite bats carry significant order and park advantages that keep their scores firmly in the \"Strong\" category. **Colt Keith** (67.49) also commands attention today, as a combination of a favorable matchup against Sandy Alcantara and a 9% SP skill bonus\u2014boosted further by the 97% stolen base threat against Alcantara\u2019s slow delivery\u2014makes him a mandatory start in our 5x5 format.\n\nWe continue to prioritize stolen base opportunities where available, though the marginal gaps between our fringe starters and our bench forced some difficult calculations. **Jerar Encarnacion** (56.19) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting lineup, missing the cut despite a massive 16% park factor boost. Ultimately, **Kazuma Okamoto** (58.71) edged him out due to the broader stability of his underlying metrics and a slightly more favorable SP skill interaction. We are also keeping a close watch on **Yordan Alvarez** (55.60) and **Josh Smith** (60.09); while **Yordan Alvarez** is facing an elite arm in Logan Gilbert\u2014which cratered his SP skill score\u2014his elite xwOBA and established BvP success mandate his inclusion. Conversely, **Hyeseong Kim** (40.38) remains benched, as the prospect of facing Jacob deGrom presents too much risk for a player who would be hitting at the bottom of the order, confirming the optimizer\u2019s decision to prioritize higher-floor plate appearances today.",
